SECURITY
We have put in place reasonable technical and organizational measures designed to secure your personal information from accidental loss and from unauthorized access, use, alteration or disclosure. However, we cannot guarantee that unauthorized third parties will never be able to overcome those measures or use your personal information for improper purposes. Also please note that email and messaging systems are not considered secure, so we discourage you from sending us personal information through these mediums. If there is a breach of security involving your credit card information from our Websites/Apps, we will inform you immediately and take commercially reasonable steps to rectify such breach.
As part of our commitment to maintaining a secure environment, we have strict policies regarding employee access to user data:
Reason and purpose of access must be provided.
Approval from a Project Manager or higher authority is required, confirming the access rights.
Data access can only be granted to employees with the explicit consent of their superior.
Storage of data on devices (laptops, tablets, etc.) and removable media (USB devices, phones, etc.) is forbidden.
Upon completion of the task, data access rights will be revoked.
In the unlikely event of a security breach involving your credit card information on our Websites/Apps, we will promptly inform you and take commercially reasonable steps to rectify the situation. Your trust and privacy are of utmost importance to us, and we are committed to continuously improving our policies and practices to protect your data effectively.
In order to bring the best and safest experience for users by many measures, all of our Applications and Games will be tested and reviewed for possible vulnerabilities every three months. We also appreciate and take other contributions to deal with vulnerabilities into account. If you have information, please contact us at: account@bravestars.com.
